Major General Benson Akinroluyo yesterday took over as the new General Officer Commanding (GOC) 3 Division of the Nigerian Army at the Maxwell Khobe Cantonment in Rukuba, Plateau State. He was Garrison Commander and Chief of Staff at the 3rd Armoured Division, and he took over from Major General Benjamin Ahanotu who has been redeployed to Defence Headquarters, Abuja. The new GOC described Ahanotu as a seasoned military officer whose landmark achievements were glaring, and assured him that he would maintain the tempo. The outgoing GOC urged troops and senior officers to be steadfast, focused, maintain the fighting spirit and cooperate with the new GOC.